A group of friends and I visited Mpire recently for a planned night out celebrating an engagement. At first, I felt a little unsure as I was not versed in what I may encounter. However, my feelings of uneasiness and hesitation were lessened upon meeting our cocktail server, Andrea. Her service and professionalism were impressive. She had a great personality and disposition, and we all actually really enjoyed her company. Our experience did not feel transactional but warm, positive, and honest. In addition, I would be remiss if I did not comment on how skilled and professional the dancers are in this club. Overall, 5 stars! By the end of the night, I felt so comfortable thanks to Andrea and the overall quality of the entertainment and service! If you ever visit Mpire, I would suggest seeing if you can request Andrea to be your cocktail server!

Went to Mpire about a month ago, and enjoyed myself immensely as the customer service was great.  The set up was a bit different than Im used to but the security seemed to always be near by and greeted me at the door.  I really was impressed by the ID scan as if something should happen I suppose they would know everyone who was there, when it did.  I assume it would keep unwanted elements from attending.  However if it weren't for my cocktail waitress Megan I wouldn't have had as good a time as I did.  She really kept checking on me, made sure I was well taken care of and her smile is infectious.  The only reason I didn't give the place 5 stars was due to a few of the dancers complaining about management when they sat down with me to chat, which was something I really could have lived without lol.  The only reason I gave it 4 stars was my impeccable  service with drinks from Megan.  I will add when I came back this past weekend to ask for her, I was told by a dancer she was no longer there.  I guess dancers and gossip go together, but understanding that the reason is an ex and a friend wrote poor reviews and management want to deal with it.  I checked it out and sure enough those reviews were there, and even I could tell those had to be reviews written by jilted love interests and disappointing that a club trying to be the premier club in the city wouldn't back their employee enough to have it removed.  Sad indeed and I can say I will no longer attend Mpire and will let my business colleagues know they should probably find another establishment or go next door to Camelot.  Still not the greatest place but at least its convenient.

I have been going to gentlemen clubs for many years in many places across the world and United States, and I must say the experience I had at Mpire was solely great due to the service I received from Meghan, and it really is the only reason I have returned over and over.  I have to say that after reading some recent reviews, it's a shame that someone would post information which has to obviously be untrue and defaming in every aspect.  For one how can one pay attention to everything Meaghan is doing if she's servicing customers as she's always on the go with a smile on her face.  Also.. how can one hear any detail of conversation with other's when the music is beyond loud.  I literally having ringing ears when I leave the establishment.  With all that being said I hope Mpire management decides to remove the slanderous reviews left for one of their best people, or it would reflect poorly on them as ownership to allow it to remain.  MPire.. customer service is everything and ask for Meghan... she does it with a smile!!
